Vector in Java
`Vector` is a class in `java.util` that implements List, RandomAccess, Cloneable, and Serializable.
It is a resizable array similar to `ArrayList`, but it is synchronized, meaning it is thread-safe for concurrent access.

#### Key Characteristics
- Maintains insertion order.
- Allows duplicate elements.
- Provides random access in constant time.
- Slower than `ArrayList` in single-threaded contexts due to synchronization overhead.
- Useful when multiple threads access the same list.
 
Categorized Methods
1. Adding Elements
●	`add(E e)` – Appends element at the end.
●	`add(int index, E element)` – Inserts at specific index.
●	`addAll(Collection c)` – Adds all elements from another collection.
●	`addAll(int index, Collection c)` – Inserts all at given index.
●	`insertElementAt(E obj, int index)` – Inserts element at index.
●	`addElement(E obj)` – Adds element at the end.
2. Accessing Elements
●	`get(int index)` – Returns element at index.
●	`firstElement()` – Returns first element.
●	`lastElement()` – Returns last element.
●	`elementAt(int index)` – Returns element at index.
●	`elements()` – Returns enumeration of elements.
3. Updating Elements
●	`set(int index, E element)` – Replaces element at index.
●	`setElementAt(E obj, int index)` – Sets element at index.
●	`copyInto(Object[] anArray)` – Copies elements into array.
4. Removing Elements
●	`remove(int index)` – Removes element at index.
●	`remove(Object o)` – Removes first occurrence.
●	`removeAll(Collection c)` – Removes all matching elements.
●	`removeElement(Object obj)` – Removes first occurrence.
●	`removeElementAt(int index)` – Removes element at index.
●	`removeAllElements()` – Clears vector.
●	`clear()` – Removes all elements.
5. Searching & Checking
●	`contains(Object o)` – Checks if element exists.
●	`containsAll(Collection c)` – Checks if all exist.
●	`indexOf(Object o)` – First index of element.
●	`indexOf(Object o, int index)` – Index from position.
●	`lastIndexOf(Object o)` – Last index of element.
●	`lastIndexOf(Object o, int index)` – Last index before position.
●	`isEmpty()` – Checks if empty.
●	`size()` – Returns number of elements.
●	`capacity()` – Returns current capacity.
●	`equals(Object o)` – Compares with another vector.
●	`hashCode()` – Returns hash code.
6. Iteration Methods
●	`iterator()` – Returns iterator.
●	`listIterator()` – Returns list iterator.
●	`listIterator(int index)` – Returns list iterator starting at index.
●	`forEach(Consumer action)` – Performs action for each element.
●	`spliterator()` – Returns spliterator.
●	`elements()` – Returns enumeration.
7. Conversion Methods
●	`toArray()` – Converts to array.
●	`toArray(T[] a)` – Converts to typed array.
8. Capacity Management
●	`ensureCapacity(int minCapacity)` – Ensures minimum capacity.
●	`trimToSize()` – Trims capacity to current size.
●	`setSize(int newSize)` – Sets new size.
9. Cloning
●	`clone()` – Creates shallow copy.
 
Java Code Demonstration

import java.util.*;

public class VectorDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Vector<String> vector = new Vector<>();

        // 1. Adding Elements
        vector.add("A");
        vector.add(1, "B");
        vector.addAll(Arrays.asList("C", "D"));
        vector.addAll(2, Arrays.asList("E", "F"));
        vector.insertElementAt("Start", 0);
        vector.addElement("End");

        // 2. Accessing Elements
        System.out.println(vector.get(2));
        System.out.println(vector.firstElement());
        System.out.println(vector.lastElement());
        System.out.println(vector.elementAt(1));

        // 3. Updating Elements
        vector.set(2, "Updated");
        vector.setElementAt("Replaced", 3);

        // 4. Removing Elements
        vector.remove(1);
        vector.remove("C");
        vector.removeElement("D");
        vector.removeElementAt(0);
        vector.removeAll(Arrays.asList("E", "F"));
        vector.clear();

        // 5. Searching & Checking
        vector.addAll(Arrays.asList("X", "Y", "Z"));
        System.out.println(vector.contains("X"));
        System.out.println(vector.indexOf("Y"));
        System.out.println(vector.lastIndexOf("Z"));
        System.out.println(vector.isEmpty());
        System.out.println(vector.size());
        System.out.println(vector.capacity());

        // 6. Iteration
        Iterator<String> it = vector.iterator();
        while (it.hasNext()) System.out.println(it.next());

        ListIterator<String> lit = vector.listIterator();
        while (lit.hasNext()) System.out.println(lit.next());

        Enumeration<String> en = vector.elements();
        while (en.hasMoreElements()) System.out.println(en.nextElement());

        vector.forEach(System.out::println);
        Spliterator<String> spl = vector.spliterator();
        spl.forEachRemaining(System.out::println);

        // 7. Conversion
        Object[] arr = vector.toArray();
        String[] strArr = vector.toArray(new String[0]);

        // 8. Capacity Management
        vector.ensureCapacity(20);
        vector.trimToSize();
        vector.setSize(5);

        // 9. Cloning
        Vector<String> cloned = (Vector<String>) vector.clone();
        System.out.println("Cloned Vector: " + cloned);
    }
}

